		@H Historical Background @L
		The city of Tarentum was founded as a Spartan colony originally named Taras in 702 BC. As was the case for Brundisium, southern Italy was a popular site for Greek colonization resulting in a variety of different city-states, or poleis, at the times when Rome waged its wars of conquest in the area. @L@L
		By the year 500 BC, the city was amongst the most populous cities in the whole world. An influential Tarentine general, or "strategos", named Archytas oversaw Tarentum being declared a hegemon over other Greek city-states in southern Italy during the city's golden age. @L@L
		The city played its part in the Pyrrhic War which saw massive battles between the Roman Republic and Greek city-state of Epirus, which owned the area at the time. The city eventually fell to the Romans in the year 272 BC via the treachery of the Greek soldiers. Afterwards, Romans demolished the city's defensive walls. @L@L
		
